              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border-2 border-primary/30 bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm font-medium">UX/UI Design</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border-2 border-primary/30 bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm font-medium">Wireframing</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border-2 border-primary/30 bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm font-medium">Prototyping</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border-2 border-primary/30 bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm font-medium">User Research</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border-2 border-primary/30 bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm font-medium">Figma</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border-2 border-primary/30 bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm font-medium">Design Systems</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border-2 border-primary/30 bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm font-medium">Accessibility (WCAG)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 7. Ready (left) -->
        <div class="relative flex gap-6 md:gap-8 md:flex-row-reverse">
          <div class="hidden md:flex md:w-1/2 md:flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="flex-1 flex gap-4 pl-14 md:pl-0">
            <div class="absolute left-0 md:left-1/2 w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-2 border-primary bg-white flex items-center justify-center -translate-x-1/2 md:translate-x-0 md:ml-[-20px] flex-shrink-0 z-10 shadow-sm" aria-hidden="true">
              <span class="text-base">🌟</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-7 bg-white border-2 border-primary/20 flex-1 transition-transform transition-shadow duration-300 ease-out hover:scale-[1.02] hover:shadow-xl">
              <h3 class="text-primary-text font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Ready for the next chapter</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I'm ready to enter the UX design field and open for <strong>full-time working opportunities</strong>. Let's create something meaningful together.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Panel: My Craft -->
      <div id="panel-craft" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-craft" data-tab-panel="craft" class="about-panel hidden" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center pt-24 md:pt-32 mb-[9.5rem] md:mb-[11.5rem] space-y-6 md:space-y-8">
          <p class="text-gray-800 text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold leading-relaxed italic mb-8 md:mb-10">
            Beyond pixels and prototypes, my design philosophy is rooted in the tactile world.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg font-normal leading-loose">
            These creative studies explore the core principles—balance, color theory, and visual rhythm. It's where my passion for art meets the precision of user-centered design.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-24 md:space-y-32 lg:space-y-40">
          <!-- Artwork 1: Ceramic coasters -->
          <div>
            <img
              src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}images/craft/coasters.jpg`}
              alt="Hand-painted ceramic coasters: landscapes, florals, and abstracts"
              width="4032"
              height="3024"
              class="max-w-full h-auto block"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <p class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center md:text-left">
              A study in composition and texture beyond the screen. These hand-painted ceramic coasters explore color theory and tactile elements through varied themes like landscapes, florals, and abstracts.
            </p>
          </div>
          <!-- Artwork 2: Diptych -->
          <div>
            <img
              src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}images/craft/diptych.png`}
              alt="Diptych: circular form split across two canvases with gold metallic accents and blue gradients"
              width="4032"
              height="3024"
              class="max-w-full h-auto block"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <p class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center md:text-left">
              <em class="text-sm block">Painted from inspiration by another artist; source/author unknown.</em>
              <span class="block mt-3">A diptych exploring visual balance through high contrast and color gradients. By splitting a singular circular form across two canvases, I experiment with how focal points and metallic accents can unite disparate elements to create a cohesive, harmonious whole.</span>
            </p>
          </div>
          <!-- Artwork 3: Stylized forest -->
          <div>
            <img
              src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}images/craft/forest.png`}
              alt="Stylized forest painting with metallic accents and cool blue palette, exploring depth and linear perspective"
              width="4032"
              height="3024"
              class="max-w-full h-auto block"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <p class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center md:text-left">
              An exploration of depth and linear perspective through a stylized forest. By using varying scales and a central focal point, I created a sense of immersion. The metallic accents against the cool blue palette highlight my focus on creating visual interest through contrast.
            </p>
          </div>
          <!-- Artwork 4: Color blocking & plant -->
